Create an isofs of the YaST2 OS Repair system
---------------------------------------------

1. copy the whole CD1 of the current SuSE Linux version to
   a directory:
   
   $ cd /nfs/CD1
   $ mount /cdrom
   $ cp -R /cdrom/* .
   $ cp /cdrom/.S.u.S.E* .

2. install the actual sources of the YaST2 OS Repair system
   to this directory:

   $ cd /local/yast2/modules/y2m_os_repair/
   $ make -f Makefile.cvs
   $ make
   $ make install DESTDIR=/nfs/CD1/suse/inst-sys

3. install gpart and copy /usr/bin/gpart to the inst-sys (the rpm
   package is on CD2 at suse/ap2/gpart.rpm):

   $ rpm -hUv /cdrom/suse/ap2/gpart.rpm
   $ cp /usr/bin/gpart /nfs/CD1/suse/inst-sys/usr/bin/gpart

4. install yast2-config-package-manager to the inst-sys (sw_single.ycp
   is required):

   $ cd yast2/modules/y2c_pkmg
   $ make -f Makefile.cvs
   $ make
   $ make install DESTDIR=/nfs/CD1/suse/inst-sys

5, copy the new version of the file y2m_inst/ycp/update/inst_rootpart.ycp
   to directory /nfs/CD1/suse/inst-sys/usr/lib/YaST2/clients/

6. create the iso filesystem of CD1:

   (let ruediger oertel do this!)

